  <h1>
   gesture_double_tap_distance
  </h1>
  This function is used to set the distance within which you have to touch/click the screen again after a single tap in order to trigger a
  <a href="../../../../The_Asset_Editors/Object_Properties/Gesture_Events.htm">
   Double Tap Gesture
  </a>
  . The distance is measured in inches and has a default value of 0.1.
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">gesture_double_tap_distance(distance);
</code></pre>
  <table>
   <tbody>
    <tr>
     <th>
      Argument
     </th>
     <th>
      Type
     </th>
     <th>
      Description
     </th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      distance
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
        Real
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The distance (in inches) to set for double tap gesture event detection.
     </td>
    </tr>
   </tbody>
  </table>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">N/A
</code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">if gesture_get_double_tap_distance() != 0.1
{
    gesture_get_double_tap_distance(0.1);
}
</code></pre>
  The above code checks to see if double tap distance for gestures is set to 0.1 inches and if it is not it sets it to that value.
